  "texts": [
    "Besides, the relationship between these parameters and driving distraction should also be considered.• Multimodal emotion regulation: The driving context is crucial to the study of emotion regulation.",
    "Unimodal emotion regulation may be ineffective due to rapid changes in driving scenarios (e.g., strong sunlight reflections can invalidate visual regulation; bumpy roads can mask tactile regulation; noisy construction sites might make auditory regulation be drowned out).",
    "Therefore, the driver's emotion regulation should be multimodal and adapt to the context.",
    "• Emotion regulation for different cultures and characteristics: Because emotions are culturally sensitive, this factor needs to be considered in the automotive HMI.",
    "Also, drivers' personality characteristics (e.g., extraversion or introversion) and emotional regulation strategies (reappraisal and suppression) preferences should also be considered."
  ],
